01:03:20,524 --> 01:03:23,004
I just couldn't seem
to work up an appetite

1318
01:03:23,084 --> 01:03:24,204
the way they did.

1319
01:03:24,284 --> 01:03:26,124
No, you mustn't blame
yourself, Mom.

1320
01:03:26,204 --> 01:03:29,004
We're not used
to that kind of food, that's all.

1321
01:03:29,084 --> 01:03:30,923
You don't...
pick up a fork

1322
01:03:31,003 --> 01:03:32,843
and dig
into a black salad.

1323
01:03:32,923 --> 01:03:34,842
You got to play
with it.

1324
01:03:34,923 --> 01:03:37,362
I don't think I could get through
coffee tonight.

1325
01:03:37,442 --> 01:03:39,282
I'm all out
of pink pills.

1326
01:03:39,362 --> 01:03:40,562
Where you going?

1327
01:03:40,642 --> 01:03:43,122
Home. I'd like to die
in my own bed.

1328
01:03:43,202 --> 01:03:44,722
What will I
tell them?

1329
01:03:44,802 --> 01:03:46,642
Make up some
clever little lie.

1330
01:03:46,722 --> 01:03:49,522
Tell Corie I'm not
really her mother.

1331
01:03:50,881 --> 01:03:52,721
We've decided to have
flaming brandy.

1332
01:03:52,801 --> 01:03:55,121
I'm afraid you must
excuse me, darling,

1333
01:03:55,201 --> 01:03:57,041
but it is
a little late.

1334
01:03:57,121 --> 01:03:58,641
You can't go.
It's early.

1335
01:03:58,721 --> 01:04:01,520
I know, but I have a 10:00
dentist appointment at 9:00,

1336
01:04:01,601 --> 01:04:03,920
and it's been
a very long evening,

1337
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:06,320
and I don't know
what I'm saying.

1338
01:04:06,400 --> 01:04:07,599
You can't do that.

1339
01:04:07,679 --> 01:04:08,879
Darling.
Good night, Paul.

1340
01:04:08,959 --> 01:04:10,159
Good night,
Mr. Velasco.

1341
01:04:10,239 --> 01:04:11,439
Good night,
Paul.

1342
01:04:11,519 --> 01:04:12,399
Good night.

1343
01:04:12,479 --> 01:04:13,679
Good night,
Corie.

1344
01:04:13,759 --> 01:04:14,959
You're not
going, too?

1345
01:04:15,039 --> 01:04:17,319
Certainly. I'm driving
Mrs. Banks home.

1346
01:04:17,359 --> 01:04:19,239
Oh, no. I mean,
it's too late.

1347
01:04:19,278 --> 01:04:20,318
For what?

1348
01:04:20,358 --> 01:04:23,398
The buses stop at 2:00.
How would you get home?

1349
01:04:23,478 --> 01:04:26,478
Why worry about that?
I'll meet that problem in New Jersey.

1350
01:04:26,557 --> 01:04:28,518
Really, Mr. Velasco,
it's very sweet...

1351
01:04:28,598 --> 01:04:29,477
Victor.

1352
01:04:29,558 --> 01:04:30,717
What?

1353
01:04:30,798 --> 01:04:33,277
If we're spending
the rest of the evening together,

1354
01:04:33,357 --> 01:04:36,197
it must be Victor. And I insist
the arrangement be reciprocal.

1355
01:04:36,237 --> 01:04:37,637
What is it?

1356
01:04:37,717 --> 01:04:39,476
What
is what?

1357
01:04:39,556 --> 01:04:40,637
Your name,
Mother.

1358
01:04:42,156 --> 01:04:43,596
It's Ethel.

1359
01:04:43,676 --> 01:04:46,436
Oh, yes. Ethel, that's right.
My name is Ethel.

1360
01:04:46,516 --> 01:04:48,955
That's better.
Are you ready... Ethel?

1361
01:04:49,036 --> 01:04:51,275
If you insist...
Walter.

1362
01:04:51,356 --> 01:04:52,515
Victor. It's Victor.

1363
01:04:52,596 --> 01:04:53,475
Yes, Victor.

1364
01:04:53,555 --> 01:04:54,635
Good night, Paul.

1365
01:04:56,155 --> 01:04:57,355
Shama shama, Corie.

1366
01:04:57,435 --> 01:04:58,315
Shama shama.

1367
01:04:58,395 --> 01:05:00,195
If you don't hear
from us in a week,

1368
01:05:00,275 --> 01:05:02,594
we'll be at the Nacional Hotel
in Mexico City...

1369
01:05:02,675 --> 01:05:04,194
Room 703.
Come on, Ethel.

1370
01:05:04,274 --> 01:05:06,114
What did he mean
by that?

1371
01:05:06,194 --> 01:05:08,513
Stop worrying, Mother.
Call me in the morning.

1372
01:05:08,594 --> 01:05:09,473
Oh...

1373
01:05:11,314 --> 01:05:13,873
How about that?
He likes her!

1374
01:05:13,953 --> 01:05:15,833
He likes my mother!

1375
01:05:17,233 --> 01:05:19,033
He'll probably
have to sleep over.

1376
01:05:20,033 --> 01:05:21,593
Paul, do you
suppose that...

1377
01:05:21,633 --> 01:05:22,873
Not my mother.

1378
01:05:27,073 --> 01:05:28,952
Boy, what a night!

1379
01:05:31,072 --> 01:05:33,912
I got an idea. Let's take the bottle
of Scotch downstairs

1380
01:05:33,952 --> 01:05:36,311
and ring all the bells
and yell "police. "

1381
01:05:36,351 --> 01:05:39,191
Huh? Just to see who comes out
of whose apartment?

1382
01:05:39,231 --> 01:05:41,591
What's the matter, darling?
Don't you feel well?

1383
01:05:41,630 --> 01:05:43,511
What a rotten
thing to do,

1384
01:05:43,550 --> 01:05:47,190
dragging your mother out like that
into the middle of the harbor

1385
01:05:47,231 --> 01:05:49,310
for a bowl
of sheep dip.

1386
01:05:52,830 --> 01:05:55,589
It was Greek bean soup.

1387
01:05:57,189 --> 01:05:59,069
And at least
she tasted it.

1388
01:05:59,109 --> 01:06:01,469
She didn't jab at it
with her knife

1389
01:06:01,508 --> 01:06:03,029
throwing cute
little epigrams like,

1390
01:06:03,108 --> 01:06:05,748
"Ho, ho, ho. I think
there's somebody in there. "

1391
01:06:05,829 --> 01:06:08,188
That's, um... quite
a match you made.

1392
01:06:08,228 --> 01:06:10,588
I can just hear the conversation.
Sparkling dialogue.

1393
01:06:10,628 --> 01:06:12,988
He's telling her about some great
Japanese restaurant

1394
01:06:13,028 --> 01:06:14,908
in East Berlin,
and she's describing

1395
01:06:14,948 --> 01:06:17,468
the joys of having
a root canal job.

1396
01:06:19,827 --> 01:06:21,347
Give me your
hand, Ethel.

1397
01:06:21,427 --> 01:06:22,307
My what?

1398
01:06:22,387 --> 01:06:24,707
Your hand. There is ice
on the stoop.

1399
01:06:24,787 --> 01:06:26,667
Don't worry about me.
I can manage.

1400
01:06:26,746 --> 01:06:27,746
Ohhh!

1401
01:06:33,106 --> 01:06:33,986
Ethel.

1402
01:06:34,066 --> 01:06:35,426
Are you all right?

1403
01:06:35,506 --> 01:06:36,545
Uhhh...

1404
01:06:36,625 --> 01:06:37,986
Ohhh...

1405
01:06:38,066 --> 01:06:39,505
Well.

1406
01:06:50,705 --> 01:06:52,064
I just can't
understand

1407
01:06:52,144 --> 01:06:54,624
how you can be so unconcerned
about all this.

1408
01:06:54,704 --> 01:06:56,423
- Unconcerned?
- I really...

1409
01:06:56,504 --> 01:06:58,983
Do you think
I'll get one wink of sleep

1410
01:06:59,063 --> 01:07:00,583
until that phone
rings tomorrow?

1411
01:07:00,663 --> 01:07:02,983
I'm scared to death
for my mother.

1412
01:07:03,063 --> 01:07:05,862
And I'm grateful there's finally
something to be scared about.

1413
01:07:07,263 --> 01:07:09,623
What I'm really
concerned about is you.

1414
01:07:11,662 --> 01:07:12,542
Me?

1415
01:07:12,622 --> 01:07:14,222
Me?

1416
01:07:14,302 --> 01:07:15,822
Yeah. I'm beginning
to wonder

1417
01:07:15,902 --> 01:07:18,261
if you're capable
of having a good time.

1418
01:07:18,302 --> 01:07:21,141
Why? Because I like
to wear my gloves in winter?

1419
01:07:21,181 --> 01:07:24,501
No. Because there isn't the least bit
of adventure in you.

1420
01:07:24,541 --> 01:07:28,340
You know what you are, Paul?
You're a watcher.

1421
01:07:28,381 --> 01:07:30,860
You're a watcher.
There are watchers in this world,

1422
01:07:30,940 --> 01:07:32,140
and there are doers.

1423
01:07:32,220 --> 01:07:34,700
And the watchers
sit around watching the doers do.

1424
01:07:34,780 --> 01:07:36,660
Tonight you watched,
and I did.

1425
01:07:36,700 --> 01:07:39,540
It was a little harder
to watch what you did

1426
01:07:39,580 --> 01:07:42,420
than it was for you to do
what I was watching.

1427
01:07:42,459 --> 01:07:44,819
You can't even relax
for one evening.

1428
01:07:44,859 --> 01:07:47,339
I don't know, Paul,
sometimes you act like a...

1429
01:07:47,419 --> 01:07:49,778
What? Hmm? A stuffed shirt?
Is that it?

1430
01:07:49,818 --> 01:07:51,018
I didn't say that.

1431
01:07:51,098 --> 01:07:52,618
That's what you
were implying.

1432
01:07:52,698 --> 01:07:53,898
That's what
you're anticipating.

1433
01:07:53,978 --> 01:07:55,498
I didn't say
stuffed shirt.

1434
01:07:55,578 --> 01:07:56,698
Mm-hmm.

1435
01:07:57,818 --> 01:07:59,497
But you're extremely
proper and dignified.

1436
01:08:03,898 --> 01:08:06,418
Proper and dignified?
When was I proper and dignified?

1437
01:08:06,497 --> 01:08:08,976
The other night at Delfino's,
you were drunk, right?

1438
01:08:09,057 --> 01:08:10,256
Right.
I was stoned.

1439
01:08:10,337 --> 01:08:12,136
Exactly. I didn't
even know it

1440
01:08:12,176 --> 01:08:14,577
until you told me
in the morning.

1441
01:08:14,656 --> 01:08:17,456
Uhh... I mean, you're a funny kind
of drunk, Paul.

1442
01:08:17,536 --> 01:08:20,816
You just sat around looking unhappy,
watching your coat.

1443
01:08:20,896 --> 01:08:22,416
I was watching
my coat

1444
01:08:22,496 --> 01:08:24,815
because I saw someone else
watching my coat.

1445
01:08:24,895 --> 01:08:27,375
If you want, I'll get drunk
for you sometime,

1446
01:08:27,455 --> 01:08:29,295
make your hair
stand on end.

1447
01:08:29,375 --> 01:08:32,654
In Harry's Bar last New Year's Eve,
I punched an old woman.

1448
01:08:32,734 --> 01:08:34,254
Don't tell me
about drunk.

1449
01:08:36,814 --> 01:08:39,893
When else? When else
was I proper and dignified?

1450
01:08:39,974 --> 01:08:41,334
All the time.

1451
01:08:41,414 --> 01:08:42,773
You're always
dressed right.

1452
01:08:42,854 --> 01:08:44,214
You always look right.

1453
01:08:44,294 --> 01:08:46,973
You always say
the right thing.

1454
01:08:47,053 --> 01:08:48,733
You're very nearly
perfect.

1455
01:08:48,813 --> 01:08:51,892
That's a rotten
thing to say.

1456
01:08:51,973 --> 01:08:54,772
Before we were married,
I thought you slept with a tie.

1457
01:08:54,852 --> 01:08:56,292
Just for formal sleeps.

1458
01:08:56,372 --> 01:08:58,732
You have absolutely no sense
of the ridiculous.

1459
01:08:58,772 --> 01:09:00,092
Like last
Thursday night,

1460
01:09:00,172 --> 01:09:03,291
you wouldn't walk barefoot with me in
Washington Square Park.

1461
01:09:03,372 --> 01:09:04,251
Why not?

1462
01:09:04,332 --> 01:09:06,211
Simple answer.
It was 17 degrees.

1463
01:09:06,292 --> 01:09:08,572
Exactly. It's very logical,
it's very sensible,

1464
01:09:08,651 --> 01:09:09,771
and it's no fun.

1465
01:09:09,852 --> 01:09:11,691
Maybe you're right.
Maybe I am

1466
01:09:11,770 --> 01:09:14,251
a little bit too proper
and dignified for you.

1467
01:09:14,330 --> 01:09:15,850
Maybe you would've
been happier

1468
01:09:15,930 --> 01:09:19,010
with somebody a little more colorful and
flamboyant... like the geek.

1469
01:09:19,090 --> 01:09:21,930
It'd be a lot more laughs than
a stuffed shirt.

1470
01:09:21,970 --> 01:09:23,170
You said I wasn't.

1471
01:09:23,250 --> 01:09:25,049
Well, you are now.

1472
01:09:25,130 --> 01:09:26,649
I'm not listening
to this.

1473
01:09:26,729 --> 01:09:29,050
I have a court case
in the morning.

1474
01:09:29,129 --> 01:09:30,330
Where are you going?

1475
01:09:30,409 --> 01:09:31,289
To sleep.

1476
01:09:31,369 --> 01:09:32,569
How can you now?

1477
01:09:32,649 --> 01:09:35,128
I'll close my eyes
and count knichis. Good night.

1478
01:09:35,209 --> 01:09:37,648
You cannot sleep now.
We're having a fight.

1479
01:09:37,728 --> 01:09:40,769
You have the fight. When you're
through, turn off these lights.

1480
01:09:40,848 --> 01:09:42,368
That gets me
absolutely insane!

1481
01:09:42,448 --> 01:09:44,528
You can even control
your emotions!

1482
01:09:44,607 --> 01:09:47,087
No, no. I'm just as upset
as you are.

1483
01:09:47,167 --> 01:09:49,967
But when I'm hungry, I eat.
When I'm tired, I sleep.

1484
01:09:50,047 --> 01:09:51,927
I've seen you
eat and sleep.

1485
01:09:52,007 --> 01:09:53,607
Not in midcrisis.

1486
01:09:53,687 --> 01:09:55,686
What crisis?
We're just yelling.

1487
01:09:55,767 --> 01:09:57,487
You don't consider
this a crisis!

1488
01:09:57,566 --> 01:09:59,726
Our whole marriage
is hanging in the balance.

1489
01:09:59,806 --> 01:10:00,686
It is?

1490
01:10:00,766 --> 01:10:02,126
When did this happen?

1491
01:10:02,207 --> 01:10:04,686
Just now. It's suddenly become
very clear to me

1492
01:10:04,765 --> 01:10:07,406
that you and I have
absolutely nothing in common.

1493
01:10:07,486 --> 01:10:09,965
Because I won't
go walking barefoot in the park?

1494
01:10:10,046 --> 01:10:12,286
No case. Adultery, yes,
but cold feet, no.

1495
01:10:12,326 --> 01:10:15,804
Don't you oversimplify this.
I am angry. Can't you see that?

1496
01:10:15,885 --> 01:10:19,205
It's 2:15. If I can get to sleep
in half an hour,

1497
01:10:19,245 --> 01:10:21,044
I'll get
about 5 hours sleep.

1498
01:10:21,125 --> 01:10:24,244
I'll call you from court tomorrow,
and we'll fight by phone.

1499
01:10:24,324 --> 01:10:25,844
You won't go to sleep!

1500
01:10:25,923 --> 01:10:28,284
You'll stay here
and fight to save our marriage!

1501
01:10:28,364 --> 01:10:30,844
If our marriage hinges
on those fishbowls and pelmenchki,

1502
01:10:30,924 --> 01:10:34,243
it's not worth saving.
Care to join me in our tiny bed?

1503
01:10:34,283 --> 01:10:36,642
We're sleeping from left
to right tonight.

1504
01:10:36,683 --> 01:10:40,482
You won't discuss it!
You're afraid to discuss it!

1505
01:10:40,522 --> 01:10:42,362
I married a...
a coward!

1506
01:10:42,522 --> 01:10:44,962
Would you bring in a pail?
The closet's dripping.

1507
01:10:45,042 --> 01:10:46,401
Oh, I hate you!

1508
01:10:46,482 --> 01:10:48,162
I really,
really hate you!

1509
01:10:48,242 --> 01:10:50,082
There's one thing
I've learned in court.

1510
01:10:50,162 --> 01:10:52,121
Be careful when
you're tired and angry.

1511
01:10:52,161 --> 01:10:54,041
You may say something
you'll regret.

1512
01:10:54,081 --> 01:10:55,641
I am now tired and angry.

1513
01:10:55,721 --> 01:10:57,241
And a coward!

1514
01:10:57,281 --> 01:10:58,361
Maybe you're right.

1515
01:10:58,400 --> 01:11:00,761
Maybe we don't have
anything in common.

1516
01:11:00,801 --> 01:11:02,200
Two people
should have more

1517
01:11:02,240 --> 01:11:04,041
than just
a blood test first.

1518
01:11:04,120 --> 01:11:06,440
Maybe they should
be checked first

1519
01:11:06,520 --> 01:11:08,360
for a little common sense,
understanding,

1520
01:11:08,440 --> 01:11:09,799
and emotional maturity!

1521
01:11:09,880 --> 01:11:12,679
All right. Why don't
you get it passed

1522
01:11:12,759 --> 01:11:14,120
by the Supreme Court?

1523
01:11:14,199 --> 01:11:17,000
Only those couples bearing a certificate
from their psychiatrist

1524
01:11:17,079 --> 01:11:19,878
proving that they're
emotionally mature can be married.

1525
01:11:21,079 --> 01:11:21,959
Oh, listen...

1526
01:11:22,039 --> 01:11:22,919
Don't touch me!

1527
01:11:22,999 --> 01:11:24,839
Don't lay
a finger on me!

1528
01:11:24,918 --> 01:11:27,238
I can't stand
to have you near me!

1529
01:11:27,318 --> 01:11:30,917
I don't want to be
in the same room with you!

1530
01:11:30,998 --> 01:11:31,877
You're hysterical.

1531
01:11:31,957 --> 01:11:32,998
I am not hysterical!

1532
01:11:33,078 --> 01:11:34,918
I know exactly
what I'm saying.

1533
01:11:34,997 --> 01:11:36,357
It's all over
between us.

1534
01:11:36,437 --> 01:11:38,757
It's never going
to be any good anymore.

1535
01:11:38,837 --> 01:11:41,157
I'm sorry.
I don't want to cry.

1536
01:11:41,237 --> 01:11:42,356
Cry, please. Go ahead.

1537
01:11:42,437 --> 01:11:44,316
Don't tell me
when to cry!

1538
01:11:44,357 --> 01:11:46,716
I'll cry when
I feel like crying.

1539
01:11:46,756 --> 01:11:49,746
I won't cry until you're
out of this apartment.

1540
01:11:49,825 --> 01:11:51,260
What do you mean?

1541
01:11:51,340 --> 01:11:55,843
You certainly don't think we're
going to live here anymore, do you?

1542
01:11:55,923 --> 01:11:56,840
After this?

1543
01:11:56,920 --> 01:11:58,434
Are you serious?

1544
01:11:58,514 --> 01:11:59,869
Of course
I'm serious, Paul!

1545
01:11:59,949 --> 01:12:01,224
I want a divorce!

1546
01:12:01,304 --> 01:12:02,460
Divorce!

1547
01:12:02,540 --> 01:12:04,214
I'm sorry.
I can't discuss it anymore.

1548
01:12:04,293 --> 01:12:05,528
Where are you going?

1549
01:12:05,608 --> 01:12:06,485
To bed.

1550
01:12:06,565 --> 01:12:07,721
You can't, not now.

1551
01:12:07,800 --> 01:12:09,196
You did before.

1552
01:12:09,236 --> 01:12:10,271
During a fight.

1553
01:12:10,351 --> 01:12:11,747
This is during
a divorce.

1554
01:12:11,787 --> 01:12:14,098
I can't talk to you when
you're hysterical.

1555
01:12:14,178 --> 01:12:17,765
I want to know why
you want a divorce.

1556
01:12:18,961 --> 01:12:19,837
Huh?

1557
01:12:22,150 --> 01:12:23,066
Why?

1558
01:12:24,541 --> 01:12:28,327
Because you and I have absolutely
nothing in common.

1559
01:12:28,367 --> 01:12:29,761
Nothing in common?

1560
01:12:29,801 --> 01:12:33,110
What about the six days
at the Plaza, Corie?

1561
01:12:33,150 --> 01:12:35,980
Six days does
not a week make.

1562
01:12:37,454 --> 01:12:39,009
What does that mean?

1563
01:12:42,237 --> 01:12:43,632
I don't know!

1564
01:12:43,672 --> 01:12:46,024
I don't know
what it means.

1565
01:12:48,933 --> 01:12:52,241
All I know is
that I want a divorce.

1566
01:12:54,672 --> 01:12:57,502
You know,
I think you mean it.

1567
01:12:57,542 --> 01:12:58,857
You mean this?

1568
01:12:58,937 --> 01:13:00,771
I do.

1569
01:13:00,851 --> 01:13:02,684
I really do.

1570
01:13:06,589 --> 01:13:08,423
Let's just...

1571
01:13:08,503 --> 01:13:09,698
think.

1572
01:13:15,199 --> 01:13:17,511
I thought you
weren't going to cry.

1573
01:13:17,590 --> 01:13:18,945
Well, I am!

1574
01:13:19,025 --> 01:13:21,336
I'm going to have
the biggest cry

1575
01:13:21,416 --> 01:13:24,206
I've ever had
in my whole life,

1576
01:13:24,286 --> 01:13:26,119
and I'm going
to enjoy it!

1577
01:13:26,199 --> 01:13:27,236
I'll cry so hard

1578
01:13:27,315 --> 01:13:29,627
I'll keep you
awake all night.

1579
01:13:29,707 --> 01:13:31,380
Good night, Paul.

1580
01:13:31,460 --> 01:13:32,816
I mean goodbye.

1581
01:14:03,824 --> 01:14:06,774
Six days does
not a week make.

1582
01:14:15,941 --> 01:14:18,731
It's for you. I don't
live here anymore.

1583
01:14:23,912 --> 01:14:25,387
Fine. Fine.

1584
01:14:26,941 --> 01:14:29,731
You work and work
for a lousy 6 cents.

1585
01:14:36,985 --> 01:14:39,775
I don't even care.

1586
01:14:39,855 --> 01:14:41,688
I don't know...

1587
01:14:41,768 --> 01:14:43,123
why I even bother.

1588
01:14:43,203 --> 01:14:45,560
It's just...
it's just nothing.

1589
01:15:26,320 --> 01:15:28,157
One pound of grapes.

1590
01:15:28,237 --> 01:15:29,116
Anything else?

1591
01:15:29,196 --> 01:15:30,594
No, thank you.

1592
01:15:40,221 --> 01:15:42,538
Ah-choo!

1593
01:15:42,618 --> 01:15:44,936
God bless him.

1594
01:15:45,015 --> 01:15:47,812
If that's for tonight,
you needn't bother.

1595
01:15:47,892 --> 01:15:49,250
I have my own dinner.

1596
01:15:49,330 --> 01:15:51,168
I thought you
were moving out.

1597
01:15:51,247 --> 01:15:55,442
I haven't had a chance
to look for a room yet.

1598
01:15:55,482 --> 01:15:56,880
I work during the day.

1599
01:15:56,920 --> 01:15:57,998
You'll look tonight.

1600
01:15:58,038 --> 01:15:59,916
I'm coming down
with a cold.

1601
01:15:59,956 --> 01:16:01,834
That's why
I'm home early.

1602
01:16:01,874 --> 01:16:05,668
I thought I'd take aspirins and get
right into the sofa.

1603
01:16:05,708 --> 01:16:07,586
I'm sure you
can find someplace.

1604
01:16:07,626 --> 01:16:09,503
You can stay
at your club.

1605
01:16:09,543 --> 01:16:12,379
It's not that kind
of a club.

1606
01:16:12,419 --> 01:16:15,256
It's a locker room
and a handball court.

1607
01:16:15,296 --> 01:16:18,692
To sleep over, I'd have
to keep winning the serve.

1608
01:16:18,772 --> 01:16:20,609
Hello, Mrs. Bratter,
Mr. Bratter.

1609
01:16:20,689 --> 01:16:22,766
How's every
little thing?

1610
01:16:22,846 --> 01:16:24,204
The little things
are fine.

1611
01:16:24,284 --> 01:16:26,641
Shall I charge it,
Mr. Bratter?

1612
01:16:26,680 --> 01:16:29,997
Charge it to Mrs. Bratter.
It's a new account.

1613
01:16:30,036 --> 01:16:31,794
The grapes are his.

1614
01:16:47,733 --> 01:16:48,772
It's open!

1615
01:16:50,450 --> 01:16:51,448
Hi.

1616
01:16:51,528 --> 01:16:52,407
Hello again.

1617
01:16:52,487 --> 01:16:53,845
Phone's out
of order.

1618
01:16:53,925 --> 01:16:55,284
Yeah. I know.

1619
01:16:55,364 --> 01:16:58,639
I wouldn't be up here
on a social call.

1620
01:16:58,719 --> 01:17:01,515
Hey, you did
a real nice job.

1621
01:17:01,595 --> 01:17:02,474
Thank you.

1622
01:17:02,554 --> 01:17:05,351
Know anybody that
might want to rent it?

1623
01:17:05,431 --> 01:17:07,268
Rent it?
You moving already?

1624
01:17:07,348 --> 01:17:09,665
I'm looking
for a smaller place.

1625
01:17:09,745 --> 01:17:12,541
Smaller than this,
they're not easy to find.

1626
01:17:12,621 --> 01:17:14,938
How do you
like married life?

1627
01:17:15,018 --> 01:17:16,176
Very interesting.

1628
01:17:18,852 --> 01:17:19,732
Hello.

1629
01:17:19,812 --> 01:17:20,850
I'm the
telephone man.

1630
01:17:20,930 --> 01:17:22,248
I'm the husband.

1631
01:17:23,926 --> 01:17:27,562
Well, let's see what's
wrong with the phone.

1632
01:17:46,097 --> 01:17:47,774
It's dead.

1633
01:17:47,814 --> 01:17:50,771
I know. It was
murdered last night.

1634
01:17:54,366 --> 01:17:57,681
I'll be out of here
as fast as I can.

1635
01:17:57,721 --> 01:17:58,800
Take your time.

1636
01:17:58,840 --> 01:18:00,917
Nobody's rushing you.

1637
01:18:06,191 --> 01:18:09,785
Is there any beer
in the house?

1638
01:18:15,738 --> 01:18:19,053
I said, "Is there any beer
in the house?"

1639
01:18:21,530 --> 01:18:24,047
Would you
like me to look?

1640
01:18:24,126 --> 01:18:26,483
There's no beer
in the house.

1641
01:18:26,563 --> 01:18:28,840
There is no beer.

1642
01:18:34,473 --> 01:18:35,672
Ah!

1643
01:18:38,787 --> 01:18:40,146
That's my trouble... beer.

1644
01:18:40,226 --> 01:18:43,981
I can drink 10 cans
in a night... of beer.

1645
01:18:51,651 --> 01:18:52,889
Ahh!

1646
01:19:04,594 --> 01:19:06,831
My laundry come back today?

1647
01:19:11,305 --> 01:19:14,101
Yes, your laundry
came back today.

1648
01:19:14,181 --> 01:19:16,858
They stuffed your shirts
beautifully.

1649
01:19:25,686 --> 01:19:28,402
Would you
like a drink?

1650
01:19:30,080 --> 01:19:32,277
I said, "Would you
like a drink?"

1651
01:19:32,317 --> 01:19:33,716
Who? Me?

1652
01:19:33,756 --> 01:19:34,754
Yeah.

1653
01:19:34,834 --> 01:19:35,793
No.

1654
01:19:35,873 --> 01:19:36,992
Right.

1655
01:19:42,464 --> 01:19:45,220
Just one more little screw
will do it.

1656
01:19:46,459 --> 01:19:47,817
There. I'm finished.

1657
01:19:47,897 --> 01:19:48,776
I'm finished.

1658
01:19:48,856 --> 01:19:51,771
Aah!

1659
01:19:55,327 --> 01:19:57,684
Hello. Yes, it is.

1660
01:19:57,724 --> 01:19:59,122
Just a moment.

1661
01:19:59,162 --> 01:20:00,560
It's Aunt Harriet.

1662
01:20:00,600 --> 01:20:03,077
I don't have
an Aunt Harriet.

1663
01:20:06,832 --> 01:20:09,668
I guess you won't
be needing me anymore.

1664
01:20:09,708 --> 01:20:10,627
Goodbye.

1665
01:20:10,667 --> 01:20:13,742
Aunt Harriet,
can you hang on a second?

1666
01:20:13,822 --> 01:20:16,539
When do I get it?

1667
01:20:16,579 --> 01:20:17,578
Get what?

1668
01:20:17,658 --> 01:20:19,335
When do I get my divorce?

1669
01:20:19,415 --> 01:20:20,335
I don't know.

1670
01:20:20,414 --> 01:20:22,052
They didn't send
the marriage license yet.

1671
01:20:22,132 --> 01:20:23,729
I want you out tonight.

1672
01:20:23,769 --> 01:20:25,168
Fine.
I'll get my bag.

1673
01:20:25,208 --> 01:20:27,085
I'll pack
my wet suits.

1674
01:20:27,125 --> 01:20:28,363
Hi, Aunt Harriet.
What's wrong?

1675
01:20:28,403 --> 01:20:30,282
I'll go sleep
in the park,

1676
01:20:30,322 --> 01:20:32,199
where it's
dry and warm.

1677
01:20:32,239 --> 01:20:34,116
No, Mother's not with me.

1678
01:20:34,156 --> 01:20:36,513
She left about
2:00 this morning.

1679
01:20:36,553 --> 01:20:39,389
Yeah? What happened?

1680
01:20:39,429 --> 01:20:40,827
What?

1681
01:20:40,867 --> 01:20:43,144
Mother?

1682
01:20:43,224 --> 01:20:44,103
My mother?

1683
01:20:44,183 --> 01:20:45,541
Are you sure?

1684
01:20:45,621 --> 01:20:47,459
What's the matter?
What happened?

1685
01:20:47,539 --> 01:20:50,814
No. My phone's been
out of order all day.

1686
01:20:50,894 --> 01:20:51,933
Don't get excited.

1687
01:20:52,013 --> 01:20:53,211
I'll call you back

1688
01:20:53,291 --> 01:20:55,608
as soon as I find out
anything. Goodbye.

1689
01:20:55,688 --> 01:20:57,046
What's wrong
with your mother?

1690
01:20:57,126 --> 01:20:58,964
Mother didn't
come home last night.

1691
01:20:59,044 --> 01:21:00,721
Her bed hasn't
been slept in.

1692
01:21:00,801 --> 01:21:01,840
I'm calling the police.

1693
01:21:01,920 --> 01:21:04,237
Take it easy.
There's nothing to be...

1694
01:21:04,317 --> 01:21:06,154
Maybe her back
was bothering her,

1695
01:21:06,234 --> 01:21:08,551
and she fell asleep
on the ironing board.

1696
01:21:08,631 --> 01:21:10,948
Would you just go away.
Just go away.

1697
01:21:11,028 --> 01:21:12,386
Where are you going?

1698
01:21:12,465 --> 01:21:14,544
Upstairs to find out
what happened to mother.

1699
01:21:14,584 --> 01:21:15,981
You better not come back.

1700
01:21:16,021 --> 01:21:18,138
I'm buying
a big dog tomorrow.

1701
01:21:18,218 --> 01:21:21,574
You'll have somebody
to walk barefoot in the park with.

1702
01:21:21,654 --> 01:21:23,052
A dog. That's a laugh.

1703
01:21:23,092 --> 01:21:25,928
When she tries
to take him for a walk,

1704
01:21:25,968 --> 01:21:27,726
he'll get one look
at those stairs

1705
01:21:27,806 --> 01:21:29,803
and go right
for her throat.

1706
01:21:32,120 --> 01:21:35,156
Mr. Velasco, can I see you
for a minute?

1707
01:21:35,196 --> 01:21:37,553
A little dog.
A little doggie.

1708
01:21:37,593 --> 01:21:39,870
I don't need anybody
to protect me, sweetheart,

1709
01:21:39,950 --> 01:21:43,945
because I am a man,
independent, mature,

1710
01:21:44,025 --> 01:21:47,140
self-sufficient
man... ah-choo!

1711
01:21:47,220 --> 01:21:49,217
Oh! God bless me.

1712
01:21:49,297 --> 01:21:51,614
I've probably got the flu.

1713
01:21:51,694 --> 01:21:53,532
Yeah.

1714
01:21:53,612 --> 01:21:56,927
Chills, fever, sweaty.

1715
01:21:56,967 --> 01:21:59,284
Probably have
a 24-hour virus.

1716
01:22:01,281 --> 01:22:04,078
Better tomorrow
at a quarter to 4:00.

1717
01:22:05,596 --> 01:22:08,073
Oh!

1718
01:22:08,393 --> 01:22:09,951
Thanks. Thanks a lot, pal.

1719
01:22:10,030 --> 01:22:11,828
And thus it was written.

1720
01:22:11,908 --> 01:22:13,745
Some shall die
by pestilence,

1721
01:22:13,825 --> 01:22:15,184
some by the plague,

1722
01:22:15,264 --> 01:22:16,302
and one poor schnook

1723
01:22:16,382 --> 01:22:19,658
will get it from a hole
in the ceiling.

1724
01:22:21,815 --> 01:22:22,694
Ahh!

1725
01:22:22,774 --> 01:22:23,972
That's it. That's it.

1726
01:22:26,489 --> 01:22:27,927
Goodbye, leaky closet.

1727
01:22:30,004 --> 01:22:32,601
Bye, no bathtub.

1728
01:22:32,681 --> 01:22:33,799
Bye, hole.

1729
01:22:35,078 --> 01:22:37,794
Goodbye, six flights.

1730
01:22:37,873 --> 01:22:38,753
Oh!

1731
01:22:38,832 --> 01:22:39,712
Goodbye,
Corie.

1732
01:22:39,792 --> 01:22:41,149
Oh, no goodbye?

1733
01:22:41,229 --> 01:22:43,107
According to law,
I'm entitled to...

1734
01:22:43,147 --> 01:22:44,026
Goodbye!

1735
01:22:45,543 --> 01:22:46,423
What?

1736
01:22:46,503 --> 01:22:48,180
Is it your mother?

1737
01:22:48,260 --> 01:22:50,577
Corie, what is it,
an accident?

1738
01:22:50,657 --> 01:22:52,534
For Pete's sake,
what's it about?

1739
01:22:52,574 --> 01:22:55,410
It's not the way
it looks at all!

1740
01:22:55,450 --> 01:22:56,330
Boo-hoo!

1741
01:22:56,410 --> 01:22:57,289
Good God.

1742
01:22:57,369 --> 01:22:59,246
Corie, you've
got to believe me.

1743
01:22:59,286 --> 01:23:00,724
Somebody believe me.

1744
01:23:04,040 --> 01:23:05,917
I warned her.

1745
01:23:05,957 --> 01:23:08,793
I warned her,
and I was right.

1746
01:23:09,233 --> 01:23:11,150
He warned me,
and he was right.

1747
01:23:11,230 --> 01:23:13,108
It must have
been the drinks.

1748
01:23:13,147 --> 01:23:15,984
I had a great deal
to drink last night...

1749
01:23:16,024 --> 01:23:18,341
Martinis, vodka, coffee,
black bean soup, and ouzos.

1750
01:23:20,818 --> 01:23:22,215
That's not
my problem.

1751
01:23:22,255 --> 01:23:24,612
I'm well
out of it now.

1752
01:23:27,528 --> 01:23:28,647
Ahh!

1753
01:23:39,353 --> 01:23:40,392
Then after I fell,

1754
01:23:40,472 --> 01:23:42,829
Victor picked me up
and carried me inside.

1755
01:23:42,869 --> 01:23:46,185
I couldn't walk because
my shoes fell down the sewer.

1756
01:23:46,225 --> 01:23:47,622
You don't have
to explain.

1757
01:23:47,662 --> 01:23:49,540
He started
to carry me here,

1758
01:23:49,580 --> 01:23:51,936
but his hat
fell over his eyes,

1759
01:23:51,976 --> 01:23:54,813
and we fell down the stairs
into apartment 3C.

1760
01:23:54,853 --> 01:23:56,251
I fell on his foot.

1761
01:23:56,291 --> 01:23:58,647
I thought we'd
have a nice evening.

1762
01:23:58,687 --> 01:24:00,566
Mr. Gonzales, Mr. Armandariz,
and Mr. Calhoun

1763
01:24:00,606 --> 01:24:02,003
carried us both
up there

1764
01:24:02,043 --> 01:24:04,400
and put us down
on the rugs.

1765
01:24:04,440 --> 01:24:06,317
When I awoke,
Victor was gone,

1766
01:24:06,357 --> 01:24:08,714
and I was there
in his bathrobe.

1767
01:24:08,754 --> 01:24:11,271
I swear that's
the truth, Corie!

1768
01:24:15,945 --> 01:24:17,344
Got a cold.

1769
01:24:17,383 --> 01:24:19,740
I've had one
for 20 years.

1770
01:24:26,491 --> 01:24:28,848
Ahh!

1771
01:24:28,888 --> 01:24:32,604
Gee, that's a nice coat
you got there.

1772
01:24:32,683 --> 01:24:34,041
What?

1773
01:24:34,121 --> 01:24:35,001
Huh?

1774
01:24:35,081 --> 01:24:35,959
Your coat.

1775
01:24:36,039 --> 01:24:39,794
I'll make you a trade.
What have you got?

1776
01:24:39,874 --> 01:24:41,552
Nothing.

1777
01:24:41,632 --> 01:24:43,029
It's a deal!

1778
01:24:45,666 --> 01:24:48,502
You must believe me.
I've told you everything.

1779
01:24:48,542 --> 01:24:49,940
Then where
are your clothes?

1780
01:24:49,980 --> 01:24:51,858
That I can't tell you.

1781
01:24:51,898 --> 01:24:52,816
Why not?

1782
01:24:52,856 --> 01:24:54,255
You won't believe me.

1783
01:24:54,295 --> 01:24:56,652
I will. Mother,
where are your clothes?

1784
01:24:56,692 --> 01:24:58,090
I don't know.

1785
01:24:58,130 --> 01:24:59,528
I don't believe you.

1786
01:24:59,567 --> 01:25:02,404
Didn't I tell you
you wouldn't believe me?

1787
01:25:02,444 --> 01:25:04,322
I don't know
where they are.

1788
01:25:04,362 --> 01:25:06,239
I've never
been so humiliated.

1789
01:25:06,279 --> 01:25:09,116
I kept having
the most horrible nightmares.

1790
01:25:09,156 --> 01:25:11,991
I kept dreaming
my fingers were falling off

1791
01:25:12,031 --> 01:25:14,788
because I couldn't
make a fist. Ohh!

1792
01:25:15,987 --> 01:25:17,264
It's me.

1793
01:25:21,698 --> 01:25:23,896
Mr. Velasco,
are you all right?

1794
01:25:23,975 --> 01:25:27,731
If a broken toe
is all right, I'm fine.

1795
01:25:27,811 --> 01:25:28,610
Hello, Ethel.

1796
01:25:28,690 --> 01:25:30,048
Hello, Victor...
Mr. Victor...

1797
01:25:30,128 --> 01:25:31,007
Mr. Velasco.

1798
01:25:31,087 --> 01:25:33,404
I couldn't get up
the ladder again.

1799
01:25:33,484 --> 01:25:35,801
Did you tell Corie
what happened last night?

1800
01:25:35,881 --> 01:25:37,238
Why? What happened
last night?

1801
01:25:37,318 --> 01:25:38,198
Ooh, last night.
Yes.

1802
01:25:38,277 --> 01:25:39,316
Take his arm,
Mother.

1803
01:25:39,395 --> 01:25:42,991
I knew I would come to this,
being helped by women.

1804
01:25:43,071 --> 01:25:45,388
Oh, dear, does
your foot hurt?

1805
01:25:45,468 --> 01:25:47,265
Compared
to my stomach, no.

1806
01:25:47,345 --> 01:25:49,662
I think I have
a new ailment

1807
01:25:49,742 --> 01:25:51,579
which I shall call
"intestinal volcano. "

1808
01:25:51,659 --> 01:25:53,976
Are there little men
in there

1809
01:25:54,056 --> 01:25:55,894
running around
in spiked shoes?

1810
01:25:55,973 --> 01:25:57,332
And pointy
steel helmets,

1811
01:25:57,412 --> 01:26:00,209
and they keep
jumping up and down, up and down.

1812
01:26:00,289 --> 01:26:03,084
How long has
this been going on?

1813
01:26:03,164 --> 01:26:04,523
Hardly ever,
except after meals.

1814
01:26:04,603 --> 01:26:05,681
Welcome to my club.

1815
01:26:05,761 --> 01:26:08,078
I think
you have an ulcer.

1816
01:26:08,157 --> 01:26:09,516
An ulcer? Me?
From what?

1817
01:26:09,596 --> 01:26:10,794
Too many
spicy foods.

1818
01:26:10,874 --> 01:26:12,233
You'll have
to get used

1819
01:26:12,313 --> 01:26:14,150
to taking
little pink pills.

1820
01:26:14,230 --> 01:26:15,588
Oh, I'd rather die,

